25:58.798 --> 26:00.731
But what if she looks in the
lake,

26:00.766 --> 26:03.423
and sees her own reflection
first?

26:03.458 --> 26:04.424
Or sees me?

26:04.459 --> 26:07.186
- I didn't get that far in the
fantasy.

26:07.220 --> 26:08.428
- This dart of yours,

26:08.463 --> 26:11.052
it takes the fun, the fun from
seduction.

26:20.130 --> 26:22.373
- Who needs firewood in August?

26:31.555 --> 26:32.418
[bell ringing]

26:32.452 --> 26:34.316
- Marlena, there's a mouse.

26:41.289 --> 26:42.704
[bell ringing]

26:42.739 --> 26:43.981
Marlena! Mouse.

26:56.684 --> 26:57.892
- Caught him.

26:58.893 --> 26:59.963
- Take him outside.

27:02.344 --> 27:05.244
- So what is all this?

27:06.866 --> 27:07.798
- Condolences.

27:08.868 --> 27:11.146
So far, I've only managed eight
replies.

27:12.976 --> 27:14.563
- So burn them.

27:14.598 --> 27:16.773
Tears are not meant to be
polite.

27:16.807 --> 27:18.015
- I don't cry, Nikolai.

27:24.297 --> 27:27.473
Timmy cursed this place
when he did what he did.

27:27.507 --> 27:29.095
- [Nikolai] So you punish Ollie?

27:31.857 --> 27:34.445
- It's easier to lose a father
than a son.

27:40.003 --> 27:41.694
- You're supposed to be helping
me.

27:41.729 --> 27:43.247
- [Nikolai] What?

27:43.282 --> 27:44.248
- Nice canoe.

27:45.215 --> 27:46.630
- [Nikolai] Fucking canoe?

27:46.665 --> 27:49.806
This a genuine Adirondack
guideboat.

27:49.840 --> 27:53.464
The Ducati of 1899. Fucking
"canoe."

27:57.054 --> 27:58.435
- Commander Sway used
to row that guideboat

27:58.469 --> 27:59.263
every morning.

27:59.298 --> 28:01.127
You could set a clock by it.

28:01.162 --> 28:01.956
What you need?

28:01.990 --> 28:03.578
- Eight cylinder head gasket,

28:03.612 --> 28:06.063
for a 1939 Criss Craft.

28:06.098 --> 28:07.340
- [Store Owner] Are you serious?

28:07.375 --> 28:08.790
That old speedboat hasn't
been out on the lake

28:08.825 --> 28:09.757
in 20 years.

28:09.791 --> 28:12.069
- [Isadora] Fucking dumb motor,
fuck this.

28:12.104 --> 28:13.415
- [Store Owner] College kids.

28:13.450 --> 28:14.727
Work at a hotel on the lake,

28:14.762 --> 28:16.522
but don't know a thing about
boats.

28:19.767 --> 28:21.872
Nice to have a fella like you on
the lake.

28:25.496 --> 28:27.084
- [Isadora] Why doesn't it
fucking work?

28:27.119 --> 28:28.292
- Let me try that.

28:28.327 --> 28:29.880
- Fuck, I don't need your help.

28:29.915 --> 28:31.848
- All right, all right.

28:38.371 --> 28:39.441
Hah, see?

28:41.305 --> 28:42.755
- I told you.

28:42.790 --> 28:44.136
Can you get out of my boat?

28:45.896 --> 28:48.140
- You know, you aren't that
friendly.

28:48.174 --> 28:51.074
- Says the guy whose friend
tried to drown someone.

28:51.108 --> 28:52.144
- He's excitable,

28:52.178 --> 28:54.940
there's a lot of freedom here,
you know?

28:58.253 --> 28:59.289
I'm Ollie.

28:59.323 --> 29:01.015
- I'm Isadora.

29:01.049 --> 29:02.292
- [Ollie] That's a pretty name.

29:02.326 --> 29:04.190
- I was named after Isadora
Duncan.

29:05.226 --> 29:06.986
Sorry about your dad.

29:07.021 --> 29:08.747
- How'd you know about my dad?

29:08.781 --> 29:10.576
- Everybody knows.

29:10.610 --> 29:11.370
- Cool.

29:11.404 --> 29:12.267
- Hey Is.

29:12.302 --> 29:13.372
Headed to The Cab this weekend,

29:13.406 --> 29:14.200
you gonna be there?

29:14.235 --> 29:15.063
- I don't know,

29:15.098 --> 29:17.100
I'm sort of like sick of
illiterates.

29:17.134 --> 29:17.928
- [Store Owner] I'll look around

29:17.963 --> 29:18.964
for a gasket for you, Nicky.

29:18.998 --> 29:20.103
- [Nikolai] Now this is a--

29:20.137 --> 29:22.415
- Hey Jim, I can't get
this piece of shit to work.

29:22.450 --> 29:23.658
- Ah, that's my kid's venture.

29:23.692 --> 29:25.073
- Dad, I fixed it yesterday.

29:27.386 --> 29:28.628
- The choke is stuck.

29:35.843 --> 29:39.329
[engine revving]

29:39.363 --> 29:40.502
- You got lucky.

29:40.537 --> 29:41.641
- All my life.

30:07.667 --> 30:08.565
- Any sign of it?

30:09.428 --> 30:10.463
- No, Mrs. Sway.

30:11.430 --> 30:13.535
But I promise, I will find it.

30:30.104 --> 30:30.932
- You realize what you've done

30:30.967 --> 30:33.107
by agreeing to work, she's a
sadist.

30:33.141 --> 30:34.211
What are you wearing?

30:35.764 --> 30:38.595
- We need to take military
action.

30:38.629 --> 30:41.460
Your purple lady has been
kidnapped!

30:42.806 --> 30:45.429
But they have revealed their
position.

31:08.349 --> 31:09.177
Kill kill kill kill.

31:13.078 --> 31:14.217
Tomorrow you die!

31:16.426 --> 31:17.599
- [Guy] Who's out there?

31:17.634 --> 31:19.912
- [Other Guy] Hey dude,
what's your problem?

31:19.947 --> 31:20.913
- Let's go.

31:20.948 --> 31:21.810
- Retreat!

31:23.122 --> 31:24.537
- [Guy] Hey, we see you man.

31:28.887 --> 31:31.717
- [Nikolai] Did your
papa teach you to fight?

31:31.751 --> 31:34.444
- [Ollie] He was neither
lover nor fighter.

31:34.478 --> 31:36.584
- [Nikolai] But your pop taught
you music.

31:37.757 --> 31:38.620
- [Ollie] I need to find a girl

31:38.655 --> 31:39.794
who likes old records.

31:41.554 --> 31:42.935
- [Nikolai] Remember when
you would do anything

31:42.970 --> 31:46.594
for a girl, because you thought
she would save your life?

31:47.767 --> 31:49.873
No woman is worth dying for
anymore.

31:49.908 --> 31:51.668
We were born too late.

31:58.847 --> 32:01.678
[melancholy love song]

32:09.134 --> 32:10.445
- If she weren't rich,
she'd just be crazy.

32:10.480 --> 32:13.345
- Why does she not go to the
dock?

32:13.379 --> 32:15.209
- She's afraid she'd jump.

32:15.243 --> 32:16.900
- And you don't swim.

32:16.935 --> 32:17.901
Runs in the family.

32:21.525 --> 32:24.114
[loon birds calling]

32:35.988 --> 32:38.473
[distant piano and orchestra]

32:50.623 --> 32:52.349
- [Hal] May the water of Sway
Lake

32:52.384 --> 32:53.868
find me in the Pacific.

33:02.014 --> 33:03.291
May 12th, 1944.

33:04.223 --> 33:05.155
Dearest Charlie.

33:08.848 --> 33:11.955
The pure water of Sway
Lake awaits our return.

33:39.879 --> 33:42.192
July 6th, 1944.

33:42.227 --> 33:43.297
Dearest Charlie.

33:46.403 --> 33:49.337
Far from these blood stained
seas,

33:49.372 --> 33:53.341
codename greatest day in
Eskimo history approaches.

33:57.656 --> 34:01.004
In love as in war, we
judge our allies best

34:01.039 --> 34:02.799
by the secrets they keep.

34:08.391 --> 34:10.703
You are a keeper of secrets,
Charlie.

34:16.951 --> 34:20.402
When I open my eyes, I see you
again,

34:20.437 --> 34:22.025
swimming toward me.

34:25.132 --> 34:27.719
I see our guests dancing in the
barn

34:27.755 --> 34:30.723
to Tweed's orchestra as
we sneak to the water.

34:35.313 --> 34:36.522
Now that you're a Sway,

34:36.556 --> 34:38.179
you and I are in cahoots

34:38.214 --> 34:40.112
to ensure that the lake remain a
place

34:40.147 --> 34:41.630
where time can stop.

34:45.290 --> 34:47.326
The music echoes in my ears.

34:50.536 --> 34:51.848
And the taste of your skin...

34:56.715 --> 34:58.579
Your devoted commander, Hal.

35:12.110 --> 35:14.940
[engines revving]

35:28.712 --> 35:31.198
[piano music]

36:14.344 --> 36:17.692
[beautiful piano music]

36:36.297 --> 36:38.575
- Would you mind looking for
Ollie?

36:38.610 --> 36:40.508
We're late for the town hearing.

36:40.543 --> 36:41.371
- Okay.

36:42.614 --> 36:43.891
- [Charlotte] Nikolai.

36:43.925 --> 36:45.444
Did you move my desk?

36:47.826 --> 36:50.587
Well, it'll have to be back
where it belongs by dusk.

36:51.416 --> 36:52.244
There's dew.

37:18.719 --> 37:20.893
- The guideboat was gone, I'll
take you.

37:20.928 --> 37:22.309
- [Charlotte] Typical Oliver,

37:22.343 --> 37:24.518
he never cared about the lake.

37:34.666 --> 37:35.494
- Hey.

37:38.980 --> 37:41.811
[old timey music]

37:45.159 --> 37:50.164
♪ Strolling along the avenue

37:51.165 --> 37:56.170
♪ Whiling the time away

37:56.998 --> 37:59.311
♪ Dreaming of all

37:59.346 --> 38:01.589
- Could you do this for me?

38:01.624 --> 38:03.315
It always comes undone.

38:03.350 --> 38:04.351
- Of course.

38:07.768 --> 38:10.046
- A large town dock will bring
new boats.

38:11.530 --> 38:12.497
Business this community needs.

38:12.531 --> 38:14.188
- That's right, Jim!

38:14.222 --> 38:15.154
[laughing]

38:15.189 --> 38:17.191
- We give the floor to public
comments.

38:22.714 --> 38:23.991
- [Woman] Mrs. Sway.

38:24.025 --> 38:26.304
- [Man] Oh, look who it is.

38:40.352 --> 38:41.180
- I...

38:42.009 --> 38:43.424
I grew up on this lake.

38:44.391 --> 38:45.530
It used to be--

38:45.564 --> 38:47.186
- [Woman] Two weeks a
year don't give you the right--

38:47.221 --> 38:48.464
- Let her talk!

38:52.847 --> 38:56.023
- It used to be this lake
connected us to the past,

38:56.057 --> 38:58.922
to nature, to each other. To
silence.

39:00.890 --> 39:03.513
First, we lost the trout.

39:03.548 --> 39:05.515
Then, most of the loons.

39:05.550 --> 39:07.897
- [Man] For God's sake, Mrs.
Sway.

39:07.931 --> 39:09.277
- While I wish Jim success

39:09.312 --> 39:11.176
with his son's jet ski business,

39:11.210 --> 39:13.558
a public dock will triple the
amount

39:13.592 --> 39:15.353
of motors on this lake.

39:16.388 --> 39:19.080
When Eel Lake got their dock,

39:19.115 --> 39:21.635
they saw milfoil come
in from outside boats.

39:21.669 --> 39:25.224
It destroyed their purple
reed, their fish stock.

39:26.156 --> 39:27.710
This isn't about a dock.

39:29.436 --> 39:31.265
This is about the water.

39:32.300 --> 39:35.649
The purity of this lake, our
lake.

39:35.683 --> 39:36.684
- [Man] You mean your lake!

39:36.719 --> 39:40.032
You don't own the lake anymore.

39:40.067 --> 39:42.518
- She is so full of it, man.

39:42.552 --> 39:45.624
[somber piano music]

40:19.244 --> 40:20.487
- You hear that?

40:20.521 --> 40:21.626
That's a 460Z.

40:21.660 --> 40:23.351
One day this lake is
gonna be a destination

40:23.386 --> 40:24.870
whether you like it or not.
Bitch.

40:24.905 --> 40:26.907
- Hey, what did you say?

40:28.874 --> 40:31.946
[somber piano music]

40:50.378 --> 40:52.519
[faint sobbing]

40:58.317 --> 41:00.492
- [Ollie] Marlena, are you okay?

41:00.527 --> 41:02.460
- You're so sweet, Ollie.

41:02.494 --> 41:03.633
Like your father.

41:05.255 --> 41:07.016
You know, he did his best for
you

41:07.050 --> 41:09.605
after your mother left you guys.

41:09.639 --> 41:11.952
But it's hard to live without
love.

41:11.986 --> 41:12.815
- I know.

41:13.850 --> 41:15.438
- He was so quiet.

41:20.547 --> 41:22.583
Did he ever show you his
collection?

41:24.827 --> 41:25.655
- Some of it.

41:29.521 --> 41:31.247
- Don't say a word, okay?

41:32.697 --> 41:36.528
But I can't find a record that
Mrs. Sway

41:36.563 --> 41:38.012
says is so important.

41:40.083 --> 41:41.982
She says she needs the money.

41:48.160 --> 41:49.058
I don't trust him.

41:57.307 --> 41:59.275
- And once again, Oliver is
missing.

41:59.309 --> 42:00.552
- I am sorry, Grandmother.

42:21.469 --> 42:24.403
[thunder rumbling]

42:26.785 --> 42:29.788
[old time Caribbean music]

42:29.823 --> 42:31.997
- [Ollie] I don't know where
else to look.

42:32.032 --> 42:33.792
- What are these markings?

42:33.827 --> 42:34.655
- Everyone in the family

42:34.690 --> 42:36.208
had their own way of ranking
records.

42:38.210 --> 42:39.349
When I was little I graded these

42:39.384 --> 42:41.524
so I wouldn't accidentally
DJ subpar music.

42:42.939 --> 42:44.078
- Olivia Newton-John.

42:44.113 --> 42:44.941
A?

42:45.770 --> 42:46.598
- What?

42:46.633 --> 42:47.461
She's hot.

42:48.566 --> 42:50.809
- [Charlotte] Thank you
Marlena, I'll take those.

42:52.086 --> 42:53.018
- Harry Belafonte.

42:53.053 --> 42:54.882
He's like the black Neil
Diamond.

42:56.677 --> 42:59.818
Julio Iglesias. He's like
the Spanish Neil Diamond.

42:59.853 --> 43:02.200
[chuckling]

43:02.234 --> 43:04.478
- [Charlotte] That is a
terribly good recording,

43:04.512 --> 43:06.238
such a handsome man.

43:06.273 --> 43:07.688
- B minus?

43:07.723 --> 43:09.207
It's not his best calypso.

43:09.241 --> 43:10.415
What are those?

43:10.449 --> 43:11.416
- For my laborers.

43:11.450 --> 43:14.730
- Oh.

43:14.764 --> 43:15.627
- Oh.

43:15.662 --> 43:16.524
Thank you.

43:17.353 --> 43:19.010
- [Nikolai] Moscow Mule.

43:19.044 --> 43:20.632
Famous American drink.

43:24.843 --> 43:27.156
- I gave it four stars.

43:27.190 --> 43:29.503
The letter grades were your
system, Ollie.

43:29.537 --> 43:33.300
I like to think I played
a part in Ollie's "calling."

43:33.334 --> 43:34.888
Now he knows what people want to
hear

43:34.922 --> 43:35.992
before they do.

43:43.655 --> 43:44.794
- Looks like we agreed on this
one.

43:44.829 --> 43:47.970
- [chuckling] Not a handsome
fellow.

43:51.111 --> 43:52.560
What grade did Timmy give it?

43:59.533 --> 44:01.949
- You know, Americans
would rather organize music

44:01.984 --> 44:03.537
than hear it.

44:03.571 --> 44:05.125
In Russia, we simply dance.

44:05.988 --> 44:08.507
Ollie, you spilled Moscow Mule!

44:08.542 --> 44:09.957
- [Charlotte] Careful.

44:09.992 --> 44:13.098
[chuckling]

44:13.133 --> 44:13.927
- What are you doing?

44:13.961 --> 44:14.824
- What are you doing?

44:14.859 --> 44:16.308
- Trying to throw her off the
scent.

44:18.863 --> 44:19.691
- [Charlotte] Oh.

44:21.624 --> 44:22.901
- Relax, I can fix it.

44:24.972 --> 44:25.801
Okay.

44:26.974 --> 44:27.803
Done.

44:31.254 --> 44:32.635
- Masterful.

44:32.670 --> 44:34.706
- I don't know how this work.

44:34.741 --> 44:36.535
- You think because I'm a woman

44:36.570 --> 44:38.814
I haven't rowed in the ocean?

44:38.848 --> 44:39.987
Of course I have.

44:40.022 --> 44:43.853
You feather your oars, and
cut right into the waves.

44:43.888 --> 44:46.028
- I swam in the Arctic Sea.

44:46.891 --> 44:47.995
Have you done that?

44:48.030 --> 44:50.895
- Try this lake, five AM in
April.

44:51.896 --> 44:55.037
Hal and I used to swim
naked every morning.

44:55.969 --> 44:59.420
The water used to be so
pure, you could drink it.

44:59.455 --> 45:03.321
- In Saint Petersburg,
when the ice turns to mud,

45:03.355 --> 45:04.563
it spits out treasure.

45:04.598 --> 45:07.739
And my pop used to take me to
the swamps

45:07.774 --> 45:09.707
to look for German corpses,

45:09.741 --> 45:12.640
clutching their G41
semi-automatics

45:12.675 --> 45:13.987
with no fucking bullets.

45:14.021 --> 45:16.783
See, what he loved about the USA

45:16.817 --> 45:19.993
is that you don't leave your
soldiers

45:20.027 --> 45:21.028
dead in the mud.

45:21.063 --> 45:23.824
You take every soldier home.

45:23.859 --> 45:25.895
And that is what makes this

45:25.930 --> 45:28.415
the greatest nation on earth.

45:30.866 --> 45:33.213
[chuckling]

45:37.010 --> 45:39.702
- Hal would've adored you.

45:41.290 --> 45:42.429
- Oh shit.

45:42.463 --> 45:43.257
- Ollie.

45:43.292 --> 45:44.534
You're so clumsy.

45:44.569 --> 45:46.019
Be careful of Hal's sweater.

45:46.053 --> 45:47.192
- Well I'm trying to clean it.

45:47.227 --> 45:49.160
- [Marlena] Here, here, here,
here.

45:49.194 --> 45:49.988
- Ollie.

45:50.023 --> 45:51.818
Here we go, here we go.

45:51.852 --> 45:52.750
Here we go.

45:53.923 --> 45:55.753
- [Charlotte] Take it.

46:01.034 --> 46:01.828
- Ollie.

46:01.862 --> 46:02.690
- You're not getting paid enough

46:02.725 --> 46:03.553
to put up with her.

46:07.454 --> 46:09.007
- [Marlena] Mice.

46:09.042 --> 46:10.906
- I'll take care of that,
Marlena.

47:25.946 --> 47:28.846
[mysterious music]

48:18.654 --> 48:20.794
[sobbing]

48:25.799 --> 48:27.111
You're not ugly.

48:48.477 --> 48:50.720
The perfect record.

48:50.755 --> 48:51.929
There you are.

49:00.178 --> 49:02.284
The one too good to hear.

49:07.220 --> 49:08.048
It's you.

49:16.022 --> 49:19.542
[old time Caribbean music
returns]

49:19.577 --> 49:20.405
Fuck.

49:32.555 --> 49:33.798
- Look at this.

49:41.737 --> 49:45.292
[mysterious ominous music]

49:50.677 --> 49:51.989
- You happy now?

50:17.324 --> 50:20.672
[old timey blues music]

50:35.101 --> 50:36.240
- [Man] Yo, you a guest here?

50:36.274 --> 50:37.275
- Goldbergs? cabin six?

50:39.381 --> 50:41.038
♪ Stick out your can

50:41.072 --> 50:45.180
♪ Here comes your garbageman

50:45.214 --> 50:46.595
♪ In the morning

50:46.629 --> 50:48.493
♪ Stick out your can

50:48.528 --> 50:52.739
♪ Here comes your garbageman

50:52.773 --> 50:54.120
♪ In the evening

50:54.154 --> 50:56.018
♪ Stick out your can

50:56.053 --> 50:58.883
♪ Here comes your garbageman

50:58.917 --> 51:00.919
- Have you seen a girl with
purple hair?

51:00.954 --> 51:02.473
Do you know where Isadora is?

51:02.507 --> 51:03.508
- Who?

51:03.543 --> 51:06.373
[saxophone music]

52:00.600 --> 52:01.394
- Are you gonna kidnap me

52:01.428 --> 52:02.326
and put me in your dungeon?

52:02.360 --> 52:03.499
- You scared the shit out of me.

52:03.534 --> 52:05.087
- I scared you?

52:05.122 --> 52:06.019
Give me those.

52:07.952 --> 52:08.780
Weirdo.

52:11.266 --> 52:12.198
Were you touching yourself?

52:12.232 --> 52:14.510
- All right, all right, give
them back.

52:26.419 --> 52:28.593
[moaning]

52:32.045 --> 52:33.805
What are you doing?

52:33.840 --> 52:35.738
- Tantric breathing.

52:35.773 --> 52:36.636
It's empowering.

52:38.224 --> 52:40.329
Are you trying to come to
the party tonight at The Cab?

52:41.813 --> 52:44.644
You should come, I'm really into
creeps.

52:44.678 --> 52:47.129
- Still not done with
cabin three, Isadora?

52:47.164 --> 52:48.613
The rest of the girls are
finished,

52:48.648 --> 52:50.167
but they don't have quite as
many boys

52:50.201 --> 52:51.064
speaking with them.

52:51.098 --> 52:52.203
- It's my fault.

52:52.238 --> 52:54.585
I was trying to get
reservations for my grandmother,

52:54.619 --> 52:56.311
Mrs. Sway from The Point.

52:56.345 --> 52:58.416
- Oh, I can help you with that.

52:58.451 --> 52:59.728
